f(x+y)+f(x-y)=2[f(x)+f(y)]\;\;\;(1).
\delta>0
C=\int_{0}^{\delta}2f(y)dy.
\begin{align*} 2\delta f(x)+C&=\int_{0}^{\delta}2[f(x)+f(y)]dy\\ &=\int_{0}^{\delta}f(x+y)+f(x-y)dy\\ &=\int_{x}^{x+\delta}f(y)dy+\int_{x-\delta}^{x}f(y)dy\\ &=\int_{x-\delta}^{x+\delta}f(y)dy. \end{align*}
